   <p><placeName ref="cwgk:P00002906">E. Town</placeName> <date when="1861-04-27">April 27. 1861</date>.
<lb/>Dear <persName ref="cwgk:N001002">Sir</persName></p>
<p>We recid your two Letters to day I regret not having the money to pay our note- If in our power- to get the 3000$ by first of <date when="1861-05">May</date> It shall be done, rest ashred that every Exurshin on our part Shall be used to pay the note off as soon as possable. any thing is so uncurtin at this time, thair is no telling what one can do</p>
<p>I have in this county Forty two Thousand Dollars- due me can not collect a Dollar</p>
<p>Your friend
<lb/><persName ref="cwgk:N00008144">S. B. Thomas</persName><pb/></p>
<p>S. B. Thomas
<lb/><date when="1861-04-27">April 27 1861</date>,</p>
